Italian 2-Year Notes Open Lower Before Bill Auction; Greek Notes Slide

-- B y   L u k a n y o   M n y a n d a   a n d   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 
2011-09-27T06:47:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/italian-2-year-notes-open-lower-before-bill-auction-greek-notes-slide.html
Italian two-year notes dropped as
the country prepared to sell as much as 14.5 billion euros
($19.7 billion) of bonds and bills.  The decline pushed the yield up by two basis points to 4.35
percent as of 7:45 a.m. in  London . The Greek two-year note
jumped 167 basis points to 72.77 percent.  Spanish securities were higher, with the two-year yield
decreasing five basis point to 3.43 percent while the 10-year
yield fell three basis points to 5.13 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lukanyo Mnyanda in Edinburgh at 
